9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 212, L.D. 312, “An Act Regarding the
10 Rates of Speed at Which School Buses Travel”
11 Amend the bill by striking out all of section 2 and inserting the following:
12 'Sec. 2. 29-A MRSA §2074, sub-§1, ¶D, as amended by PL 2005, c. 577, §30, is
13 further amended to read:
14 D. Forty-five miles per hour on all other public ways unless otherwise posted; and.'
15 Amend the bill by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or section
16 number to read consecutively.
17 SUMMARY
1188 This amendment maintains the maximum speed limit on public ways at 45 miles per
1199 hour, except when otherwise posted or when traveling in school zones; certain
2200 intersections; business, residential and built-up districts; interstate highways; and the Maine
2211 Turnpike.
